<item>
            <title>[TIKA-211] memory issue in ExcelExtractor</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-211</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The excel extractor consumes lots and lots of memory when given an excel file containing a lot of numeric cells. I tested using a simple sheet containing 254 columns and 5511 rows resulting in an 8MB big file, this blowed with an OOME when given 512MB.&lt;br/&gt;
The memory issue is caused by the java NumberFormat that is instantiated for every numeric cell. A solution would be to cache the NumberFormat instance in the TikaHSSFListener class. Since NumberFormat is not thread-safe, it might be necessary to pool it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
